exercise.statement:
        {{#scenario}}
            {{#phrasing1}}


                    {{name}} needs to select {{r}} students from a class of {{n}} students to retrieve supplies from the supply room. How many groups of students are possible?

            {{/phrasing1}}

            {{#phrasing1a}}


                    The board of trustees at {{School}} consists of {{n}} people. During the spring, a delegation of {{r}} trustees will be assigned to an outreach committee. How many such delegations are possible?

            {{/phrasing1a}}

            {{#phrasing2}}


                    {{name}}'s Bridge Club is choosing among {{n}} unique prizes for their upcoming tournament. If each of the first {{r}} places will receive a prize, how many possible ways can the prizes be handed out?

            {{/phrasing2}}

            {{#phrasing2a}}


                    Assignments are about to be made for {{r}} distinct roles in the upcoming play at {{School}}. During auditions, {{n}} people tried out. How many different castings are possible?

            {{/phrasing2a}}
        {{/scenario}}


{{Prompt}}



        Show all of your steps, specify which formula you used, and state why you used it.
